H1> Forum administration

P> Forums are organised under [b]parents[/b] (categories), with optional moderators, tracking and pruning policies per forum.

SHOT> forums/forum-admin.png | Forum tree with parents and child forums

Q> What are forum parents?
A> A parent is a heading used to group other forums together. Parents make navigation easier when you have many forums.

H1> Moderation

Q> I want to make a certain administrator a forum moderator but their name isn't in the list – why?
A> An administrator only appears as a candidate moderator if they hold the [b]Moderate forums[/b] permission. Open [b]Admin → Administrators[/b], edit the admin and tick that permission.

Q> What are reported posts?
A> Users can flag posts they consider objectionable. The reported thread appears in the moderation queue where you can read it in context and act (delete, lock, warn the user, etc.).

H1> Subscriptions and clean-up

Q> What's tracking?
A> When tracking is enabled, users can subscribe to a thread and receive an email whenever a new reply is posted.

Q> What's pruning?
A> Pruning automatically removes threads that have not received a reply within a configurable timeframe.

WARN> Pruning is destructive – deleted threads cannot be recovered. Test on a low-traffic forum first and keep regular database backups.
